Date: Wed, 1 Jul 2026 16:24:42 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 35/35] test(claim-gate): MAC-isolated red-team regressions
 (A22d/A23c/A6c)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

A load-bearing audit + real mutation test found three MAC red-team
tests were DECORATIVE: their forged ledger entries died at an earlier
structural check (wrong claimCeiling / missing nonce) and never reached
the MAC comparison — neutralizing the MAC left A22c/A23b/A6 still green.
Added MAC-isolated companions that plant an entry well-formed in EVERY
field (correct kind/claimCeiling/authority/nonce + payloadHash that
genuinely equals sha256(payload)) with ONLY the mac bytes wrong, so the
final timingSafeHexEqual is the only thing that can reject it.

Verified load-bearing by mutation (independent of the author): with the
MAC neutralized, A22d flips to failing (guard claim-gate-loop.ts:325)
and A23c flips (proof/claim-gate-loop.ts:3109), while the old decorative
A22c/A23b still pass. Guards restored; redteam suite 21/21.

